questiondata.strat-other: Occassionally, a string of words in a row made a funny expression or oxymoron-like phrase that was humorous and made it easier to remember that group of words. Paying attention to the way the speaker said some of the words differently than I would say them (with a different emphasis) helped me remember some of the words.
